                    <comment id="12596000" author="zwu_ca" created="Mon, 12 May 2008 08:55:28 +0100"  >&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;More information:  After more experiments, I found my WebDav client ( and most of others) don&amp;#39;t handle the encoding correctly-- they didn&amp;#39;t encode the command in utf-8.  I tried to use Microsoft Vista folder and it correctly handles the uploading problem. It is not Jackrabbit WebDav&amp;#39;s problem.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The only thing left is the search.jsp. I&amp;#39;m not sure this is the problem for Jackrabbit. It is probably more general problem for jsp or  web broswer(IE and FireFox): why is the parameter sent from the clients not encoded in utf-8 even the page is specifically a utf-8 page?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Anyway, this becomes a minor problem and can be worked around.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;</comment>
